<div class="penelope">
  <img src="/img/welcomingcat.png" alt="Penelope the Neocities cat">
  <div class="penelope-Bubble">
    <p>Color names are fun, but there are only 140 of them. Time to unlock the other 16 million.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<p>A <strong>hex code</strong> describes any color the screen can make: a <code>#</code> followed by six characters &mdash; two for <span style="color:#c0392b;font-weight:bold">red</span>, two for <span style="color:#27ae60;font-weight:bold">green</span>, two for <span style="color:#2980b9;font-weight:bold">blue</span>, each from <code>00</code> (none) to <code>ff</code> (maximum):</p>

<pre><code class="css">body {
  background-color: #ffe9f0;
}</code></pre>

<p>You never have to invent these by hand &mdash; color pickers speak hex for you. Here, try this one: slide to a hue, drag around the square, and copy the code of anything you love.</p>

<div class="color-Picker">
  <div class="picker-Area" id="pickerArea" tabindex="0" aria-label="Color square. Use the arrow keys to adjust the color.">
    <div class="picker-Thumb" id="pickerThumb"></div>
  </div>
  <input type="range" id="pickerHue" class="picker-Hue" min="0" max="360" value="341" aria-label="Hue">
  <div class="picker-Result">
    <span class="picker-Swatch" id="pickerSwatch"></span>
    <code class="hljs" id="pickerHex">#ffe9f0</code>
    <button type="button" id="pickerCopy" class="picker-Copy">Copy</button>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Or start from one of these:</p>

